  "justification": "doStandardCalcs(field, ignoreNulls, nullAsZero) is the default standard-calculations reducer. It takes a Field object (with a values array and type enum) plus two boolean flags (ignoreNulls and nullAsZero). It returns a FieldCalcs dictionary with: first, last, firstNotNull, lastNotNull, min, max, sum, count, nonNullCount, mean, range, diff (lastNotNull - firstNotNull), diffperc (percentage change), delta (cumulative positive increments with counter-reset detection), step (minimum interval between consecutive non-null values), logmin (smallest positive value), allIsNull, and allIsZero. The procedure: (1) returns defaultCalcs immediately if data is empty/undefined; (2) checks field.type for number or time to set isNumberField; (3) iterates all values recording first/last, handling nulls per the two flags, incrementing count; (4) for non-null numeric values tracks sum, min, max, logmin, nonNullCount, step (minimum gap), and delta (accumulating positive increments while detecting counter resets via previousDeltaUp); (5) after the loop clamps sentinel values (-MAX_VALUE/MAX_VALUE) back to null, then computes mean, range, diff, and diffperc."
}

